<div id="pf5f" class="pf w4 h41" data-page-no="5f"><div class="pc pc5f w4 h41"><img class="bi x0 y0 w5 h42" alt="" src="bg5f.png"/><div class="t m29b x35 h1d ya42 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Overshadowing Providence </div><div class="t m77 xa4 h1d yb11 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m116 xce h1d ya42 ff2 fs12 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">March 30 </div><div class="t m21f x27 h1a yafc ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">10. Read 2 Samuel 22:35-43 in light of the principles of the great </div><div class="t m12e x21 h1a y107 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">controversy between Christ and Satan. (See Rev. 12:1-17.) How </div><div class="t m12c x21 h1a yafd ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">would you explain the following? </div><div class="t m198 x28 h1b yaff ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;He teaches my hands to make war&quot; (2 Sam. 22:35, NKJV; see Eph. </div><div class="t m254 x27 h1b yb12 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6:10-17). </div><div class="t m5da x12 h1b yb13 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;You have subdued . . . those who rose against me&quot; (2 Sam. 22:40, </div><div class="t m273 x27 h1b y54e ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NKJV; see Rev. 12:9-11). </div><div class="t m4d8 x12 h1b y93d ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;I beat them as fine as the dust of the earth&quot; (2 Sam. 22:43, NKJV; </div><div class="t m276 x29 h1b y553 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">see Ps. 2:8, 9; Rev. 19:15). </div><div class="t m237 xcd h1c yab ff2 fs11 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">WED </div><div class="t m620 x29 h1a y556 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">11. Summarize in your own words some of the reasons David had </div><div class="t m273 x2d h1a y2b9 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for being grateful: </div><div class="t m367 x56 h1b y2ba ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2 Sam. 22:20, 44 </div><div class="t m77 xa5 h1b y2ba ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mec xa9 h1b y2ba ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m3d8 x56 h1b yb14 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 26-28 </div><div class="t m77 x2a h1b yb14 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mec xa9 h1b yb14 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m325 x56 h1b yb15 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 29-31 </div><div class="t m77 x2a h1b y2be ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mec xa9 h1b y2be ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m23d x56 h1b yb16 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 36, 37 </div><div class="t m77 x2a h1b yb16 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mec xa9 h1b yb16 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m25f x56 h1b yb17 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 50, 51 </div><div class="t m77 x2a h1b yb17 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mec xa9 h1b yb17 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m2dd xb h1b yb18 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Deitrich Bonhoeffer, who spent the last years of his life in a Nazi prison </div><div class="t m24a xf h1b y121 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">camp and eventually became a martyr, loved and read the psalms daily. A </div><div class="t m395 xf h1b y122 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">friend who was with him in his last days said that he seemed to diffuse </div><div class="t m551 xf h1b y123 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">happiness and joy to those about him, and manifested a deep sense of grati-</div><div class="t m2a9 xf h1b yb19 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tude over just being alive. He had learned well the lesson of the psalmist: </div><div class="t m3af xf h1b y125 ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">gratitude born of adversity sings God&apos;s praises from the heart, not just with </div><div class="t m162 xf h1b yb1a ff5 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the lips. </div><div class="t m1a1 xf h1a y2c5 ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">IV. DAVID THE PROPHET (2 Sam. 23:1-7). </div><div class="t mc1 xf h1a yb1b ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">12. </div><div class="t m5f1 x56 h1a yb1b ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What New Testament criteria confirms David&apos;s prophetic gift? </div><div class="t m3ee x56 h1a yb1c ff1 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Who was the &quot;Rock of Israel&quot; who spoke to him (2 Sam. 23:1-</div><div cl